			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can also confirm that you only need to kill the nastiest ofthe warewolves (the highest con).  A decent bard will be able to split the mobs down to the one needed.
<br />

<br />
That spawns the Shady Bandit.
<br />

<br />
The Warewolf is very resistant to slow, Disease slow won't land at all with standad debuffs. In the end had to have a Chanter (Tash) + Shammy (Malo) + Bard (some debuff <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />) to get slow to land. Once it does its a piece of cake (relitively for a 1200 hitting mob <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />)
<br />

<br />
Force that I used was : 
<br />

<br />
Chanter
<br />
Bard
<br />
Shammy
<br />
Ranger
<br />
Wizard
<br />
Cleric
<br />
Warrior
<br />
Necro (Me)
<br />

<br />
Nearly all were Time+ equiped, Had no real issue with either fight.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
