			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">well, took a small group and tried this tonight, and failed, because I was pretty sure we didn't have the numbers, but thought I'd give it a shot anyway.
<br />

<br />
Did QVoX, then turned in, werewolves spawned just a short distance away (a little north of east of Yuanda) about 1 tick later.  And they all started running towards the southwest.  Got proximity agro shortly there after and started to run them away.  Shaman quickly picked the 72nd level mob out of the pack (yellow to her 70, red to my 69) and maloed and pulled him to group while the other 4 lessers followed me along.  I fd, and our ranger started to kite around the lessers.  Meanwhile, shaman unable to land slow, and not having a dedicated healer, the paladin died fast, followed quickly by the shaman.  The 72 then reagroed on the ranger and she pulled them all to the NK zoneline.  Fortunately, the 72 was not near the other 4, and after getting everyone rezzed, I attempted to learn a few things about it.
<br />

<br />
scent of midnight landed first shot, although, think malo was still active on him, so that may have definitely helped.  fpok and bot both landed first time.  and then I found out the mob summons. &gt;:)
<br />
he hit me for three rounds, 1 set of two attacks, and 2 sets of 4 attacks each.  only 2 of the hits did he ever max 1150 (shaman confirmed this max hit too)
<br />

<br />
So, the full ticks of fpok and bot got him down to 94%.  and then after fd wiped agro, got up, sent in pet to buy me some casting time, and by that time, I believe malo had worn off, cause fpok and bot did not land (and the ranger's swarming death didn't land either), but fang of death did land.  fod took him down further to 91%.  btw, his regen sucks, it's like old world mob regen.  A quick estimate of the damage done by the spells puts his total HPs slightly over 100K.
<br />

<br />
Other things to note: none saw invis, and in that small time where anyone got hit by him, he did not rampage or flurry.
<br />

<br />
One thing to note tho, while kiting the four away from the group, I got sloppy and let them catch me after DA wore off.  They all got a nice round of hits in, but I got away, but did notice that they all got the ds spam 'xx is pierced by thorns'.  So I'm wondering if even though they always get missed by melee, the mage pyrilen's skin would be a nice bonus to the tank tanking him.
<br />

<br />
next time, won't go at him with less then what I feel is the required people/classes.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=399617" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img115.exs.cx/img115/2075/agro1bp.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
