			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">i underestimated this part and brought only a few caster classes because i thought it's going to be easy. if i have to rate this mob, i would perhaps put him above Viarglug.
<br />

<br />
group only consists of 7 people:
<br />

<br />
druid
<br />
necro
<br />
warrior
<br />
cleric
<br />
enchanter
<br />
shaman
<br />
rogue
<br />

<br />
funny thing is, rogue can confirm that his discipline allows him to get a few good Backstabs in (lol), even though only in about 1 out of 3 or 4. mob dies really really slow and i wished i have a mage or wiz dps with the group.
<br />

<br />
to split the mob, i first tried to snare-split him. after 30 resisted snares, i just gave up and asked the druid to kite the other 4 away while i kite the named. after splitting the named from the rest for some distance, druid evaced. then we engaged named without interruption.
<br />

<br />
i learned later from a fellow nec (Zsher) that you could just simply bring the named to the NK zoneline solo. and zone out whenever you are OOM. zone back in again (invised of course). and just med up till you are ready to fight again (since the mob regen is REALLY SLOW). this is a pretty good idea to use if MT or cleric went OOM.
<br />

<br />
remember the 30minutes timer though.
<br />

<br />
rumor is, tomorrow's patch gonna make this encounter a bit harder as well as some other tweaks in different parts of the quest....<br />_________________<br />Voydent
<br />

