			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Okay I had to do the Werewolf encounter quite a few times, so here's all what I gathered and anyone should be able to do this now.  You turn the note into Yuanda and it spawns 5 snarling werewolves.  As soon as you turn it in, FD.  The werewolves are Paciable by the level 67 Druid Pacification.  Single pull named...
<br />

<br />

<br />
OR you can AE snare on pull, and end up getting most ("named" wolf will not snare or is super resistant) and run the wolves wherever you like.  You don't need them, so your kiter could bring them to zone line if he wants.  Their agro is not linked, they corpse camp, they despawn in 30 minutes and they do NOT regen.  Magic based spells worked fine.  My tank said that he figured the werewolf was in constant furious mode (I won't kid myself, I don't know the nitty gritty about tanks, but that's what he said : P)  Yuanda respawns as soon as wolves Despawn if you fail, so woohoo for that.  You'll need another note if you failed.  After you killed the 'named' wolf, you MUST kill the bandit in the southern end of zone as he will despawn within 30 minutes.  
<br />

<br />
FYI all wolves summon so DON'T accidentally hurt the lower ones, having them summon left and right is a biiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiig PITA.  I wouldn't even mezz and keep them around, takes too long to kill them, is pointless, and is just another paranoia.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
