			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Of the pre-epic encounters the werewolf one is by far the hardest, imo, because it takes a while to bring the boss werewolf down due to his near total melee mitgation.  Bring caster dps and enough healing.  We wiped on it with 8 pre-elemental players due to the healers not having enough mana.  The next time we tried it with 15 and that was plenty, though the 2 clerics were still getting low on mana by the end (lasted close to 10 mins I think).  It took our enchanter and shaman close to 3 minutes before they landed slow.  I also had trouble landing magic-based spells so it's MR is high.
<br />

<br />
Using 2 FDers it's very easy to split out the red werewolf.  When you do the turn-in you can avoid aggro by immediately running to the east (keep the main party to the south out of aggro range).  The werewolves will stop at Yuanda's location.  I had my wife's monk start the pull toward the east while I stood to the west (but close enough to cast after they started running).  I then cast snare on the red werewolf (resisted) and he came after me.  We both FD and waited for aggro to clear and the red wolf was now single.  Bring along an invis potion (or CoS) for the pullers so they can stand up without getting aggro again.
<br />

<br />
If you put together a group that can take down the werewolves then you can do the next 4 pre-epic fights in no time.  Took us around 1.5 - 2 hours to do them all counting gathering, buffing and traveling time.
<br />

<br />
Sivas</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
