			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Had a funny thing happen after we killed the Werewolves. Ran south to the bandit camp for the Shady Bandit. Found him just south of the bandit camp. He was standing by a tree.
<br />

<br />
Four of my mini raid were there waiting for the rest of the team to catch up. Then one of the guys helping me says in general say: "Is this the guy you have to kill? Ohh, he hates me."
<br />

<br />
I replied in general say, " Yep, he is kos to everyone but will not attack until I hail him."
<br />

<br />
BLAM!!!! I got hit with a life tap! 
<br />

<br />
Here's the cool thing that happened though. In my excitment of killing the Werewolf I neglected to put the breaks on my pet using AA command! HAH! He immediatly attacked the Shady Bandit and stopped him in his tracks as he was headed for me. Now no one in the mini raid had known what was going on, it really happened so fast and took everyone off guard. I hit FD and killed my pet (Lost Soul). My melee's had not shown up yet but since no one else got involved the bandit stood still and made no further attack. When the melee's arrived I simply said kill it and we did!
<br />

<br />
Reminds me of standing in a Wayfarers camp and someone /ooc's "How do I get to ...."
<br />

<br />
*Poof*
<br />

<br />
*oops*</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
